						<summary>

						<p>The king has the attribute “who was pleased to take Madurai”. This records a similar gift of 7 <hi rend="italic">mā</hi> of land in the same place for a perpetual lamp in the temple, by one Arayaṉ Tiruvanantaṉ Kēraḷarāmaṉ of Kiḻvēṅgai-nāḍu in Rājarāja-vaḷanāḍu.</p>						

